I'll do some grocery shopping tomorrow.

34
00:07:10,783 --> 00:07:12,285
Just have them delivered.

35
00:07:12,994 --> 00:07:14,370
I did that, too.

36
00:07:46,527 --> 00:07:47,612
It's gone bad.

37
00:09:41,225 --> 00:09:43,686
I'm not having breakfast, don't bother.

38
00:09:49,817 --> 00:09:50,902
I'm off.

39
00:09:52,069 --> 00:09:53,821
Have a fried egg at least!

40
00:09:54,489 --> 00:09:55,406
See you tonight.

41
00:09:56,115 --> 00:09:57,450
Damn it.

42
00:10:20,598 --> 00:10:24,310
{\an8}SANPO CITY

43
00:10:31,275 --> 00:10:32,318
{\an8}The bus is here.

44
00:10:46,165 --> 00:10:47,542
{\an8}It's my treat today.

45
00:10:48,251 --> 00:10:50,753
{\an8}Why would you treat us? It's fine.

46
00:10:52,129 --> 00:10:54,465
{\an8}I should since you came all the way
to the funeral.

47
00:10:56,634 --> 00:10:59,971
{\an8}Mi-jeong, I didn't know you lived
that far away. It took forever.

48
00:11:00,054 --> 00:11:02,890
{\an8}It's 29 stops. I counted it myself.

49
00:11:03,516 --> 00:11:05,434
{\an8}How do you commute from there every day?

50
00:11:07,853 --> 00:11:09,355
{\an8}Where did you put your mom's urn?

51
00:11:10,648 --> 00:11:11,732
{\an8}At home.

52
00:11:14,735 --> 00:11:17,280
{\an8}Her urn is at your house?

53
00:11:19,991 --> 00:11:21,158
{\an8}Is that okay?

54
00:11:22,702 --> 00:11:23,911
{\an8}Why wouldn't it be?

55
00:11:24,787 --> 00:11:25,997
{\an8}Isn't it illegal?

56
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,623
{\an8}No, it isn't.

57
00:11:27,707 --> 00:11:28,958
{\an8}I see.

58
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,835
{\an8}I heard it was illegal to scatter them.

59
00:11:31,502 --> 00:11:35,006
{\an8}Aren't the urns also managed
in some system or something?

60
00:11:35,089 --> 00:11:38,301
What do you think dying is?
It means you're out of the system.

61
00:11:41,762 --> 00:11:43,222
Why not a columbarium?

62
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:48,227
How could we leave her somewhere else?

63
00:11:51,814 --> 00:11:53,566
So it's okay to keep it at home.

64
00:11:55,693 --> 00:11:56,902
Isn't it scary?

65
00:12:05,578 --> 00:12:07,371
It still doesn't feel real, does it?

66
00:12:11,917 --> 00:12:13,544
I still don't know what's going on.

67
00:12:15,254 --> 00:12:17,089
The ambulance came that day

68
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:21,135
and said they don't move patients
who are in cardiac arrest.

69
00:12:22,470 --> 00:12:25,681
We asked them desperately
to take her to the hospital,

70
00:12:26,599 --> 00:12:27,975
but they said they couldn't.

71
00:12:30,978 --> 00:12:34,106
Then the police came
to see my mom lying in the bedroom.

72
00:12:35,524 --> 00:12:37,234
They asked weird things like,

73
00:12:37,318 --> 00:12:40,237
"Did you have a fight?"
"How many insurance policies do you have?"

74
00:12:42,323 --> 00:12:45,743
That's a really odd experience.

75
00:14:42,193 --> 00:14:44,570
AUNTIE X

76
00:14:51,452 --> 00:14:52,328
Hello?

77
00:14:52,411 --> 00:14:55,164
<i>Why didn't you pick up?
I've been calling you since before.</i>

78
00:14:56,207 --> 00:14:57,625
I was busy.

79
00:14:57,708 --> 00:15:01,045
<i>I fried some anchovies and shrimp.
Pick them up when you finish work.</i>

80
00:15:01,128 --> 00:15:03,130
Dad doesn't like dry dishes.

81
00:15:03,214 --> 00:15:07,218
<i>Hey, your father's a widower now.
Tell him to eat whatever's offered.</i>

82
00:15:07,301 --> 00:15:08,469
<i>Just come and take them.</i>

83
00:15:10,846 --> 00:15:12,098
This damn…

84
00:15:34,787 --> 00:15:35,788
Welcome.

85
00:15:36,914 --> 00:15:39,834
I'll have 300g of beef for soup
and 2.4kg of pork ribs.

86
00:15:39,917 --> 00:15:42,795
I see. 300g of beef for soup
and 2.4kg of pork ribs.

87
00:15:45,089 --> 00:15:46,465
Actually, make it 3kg.

88
00:15:46,549 --> 00:15:48,300
-3kg of pork ribs, right?
-Yes, please.

89
00:15:48,384 --> 00:15:49,385
Coming right up.

90
00:16:04,608 --> 00:16:06,277
Why didn't you just take a taxi?

91
00:16:10,197 --> 00:16:11,532
We're home.

92
00:16:11,615 --> 00:16:12,491
We're home.

93
00:16:34,054 --> 00:16:35,389
Damn it.

94
00:17:01,957 --> 00:17:05,002
Hey, Mom definitely died from overwork.

95
00:17:14,678 --> 00:17:17,640
Why do I have to go all the way
to Wangsimni to pick up some food?

96
00:17:18,349 --> 00:17:21,769
She doesn't even know what you like.
She just pretends to care.

97
00:17:22,519 --> 00:17:24,563
I almost threw them out on my way home.

98
00:17:24,647 --> 00:17:25,689
That's enough.

99
00:17:25,773 --> 00:17:29,318
I know she doesn't care about you.
Why does she have to pretend she does?

100
00:17:33,614 --> 00:17:35,824
She must be doing this
to get money from you.

101
00:17:36,408 --> 00:17:39,161
If she even talks about it,
I'll go show her what's what.

102
00:17:40,162 --> 00:17:42,665
-There's nothing stopping me now.
-Seriously…

103
00:17:43,832 --> 00:17:46,293
Don't you know
who put Mom through all that?

104
00:17:48,295 --> 00:17:50,422
Just let Dad eat!

105
00:17:54,885 --> 00:17:56,553
Give me your seal later, Dad.

106
00:17:56,637 --> 00:17:59,056
We'll go and bury it somewhere.

107
00:18:00,766 --> 00:18:04,645
If you let your sister
have her way again, we're done.

108
00:18:05,479 --> 00:18:08,482
I don't even care if we're family.
I won't see you again!

109
00:18:19,368 --> 00:18:22,121
LATE KWAK HYE-SUK

110
00:18:50,399 --> 00:18:51,692
Thank you.

111
00:18:51,775 --> 00:18:53,736
-Thank you, boss.
-Goodbye.

112
00:18:53,819 --> 00:18:55,487
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

113
00:18:55,571 --> 00:18:56,864
I had a great time.

114
00:19:00,534 --> 00:19:02,161
How's Gi-jeong doing?

115
00:19:02,995 --> 00:19:05,039
I mean, she used to come every day.

116
00:19:06,498 --> 00:19:07,624
I kind of miss her.

117
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,252
She goes straight home
after work these days.

118
00:19:10,919 --> 00:19:14,089
Yes, she should.
Her father must be lonely by himself.

119
00:19:14,965 --> 00:19:16,091
He's not alone.

120
00:19:16,175 --> 00:19:18,719
I heard her brother quit his job
and stays at home.

121
00:19:20,596 --> 00:19:23,474
Goodness, it's a pity
she passed away so soon.

122
00:19:23,557 --> 00:19:25,893
You didn't even get to meet her.

123
00:19:26,685 --> 00:19:27,519
I did.

124
00:19:32,858 --> 00:19:34,318
The day she passed away.

125
00:19:35,069 --> 00:19:36,236
In the afternoon.

126
00:19:37,571 --> 00:19:38,989
She bought me lunch.

127
00:19:45,412 --> 00:19:49,625
To think that someone I saw
in the afternoon passed in the evening…

128
00:19:55,381 --> 00:19:58,300
She must have wanted
to meet her son-in-law before she left.

129
00:20:12,272 --> 00:20:14,149
{\an8}How could you say that in front of her?

130
00:20:20,739 --> 00:20:22,157
{\an8}So I looked at the envelope,

131
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:25,411
{\an8}and it said "Park Jin-u."

132
00:20:27,287 --> 00:20:30,541
{\an8}So I was like, "What?" And I looked up.

133
00:20:30,624 --> 00:20:33,585
{\an8}And he said, "Ms. Yeom Gi-jeong
bad-mouthed me a lot, didn't she?"

134
00:20:38,298 --> 00:20:41,218
{\an8}All the people I've heard so much
about were gathered there,

135
00:20:41,301 --> 00:20:44,513
{\an8}so I kind of got excited
and put my foot in my mouth.

136
00:20:45,973 --> 00:20:49,351
{\an8}I was like,
"So this is what a funeral can be like."

137
00:20:49,435 --> 00:20:50,644
{\an8}I told you, right?

138
00:20:51,353 --> 00:20:55,983
{\an8}That the girl Gi-jeong said had "nasty"
written all over her face must be pretty.

139
00:20:56,733 --> 00:21:00,612
{\an8}I picked her out immediately among
all her colleagues. "It's her!"

140
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,614
{\an8}So I asked Gi-jeong,

141
00:21:02,698 --> 00:21:07,411
"The girl who has 'nasty' written
all over her face. That's her, right?"

142
00:21:07,494 --> 00:21:08,537
And she said,

143
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:11,039
"Yes."

144
00:21:11,123 --> 00:21:15,419
It came out that she lied, you know?

145
00:21:29,975 --> 00:21:32,352
I was even more shocked
when your mom passed away

146
00:21:32,853 --> 00:21:35,731
than when my mom passed away.

147
00:21:37,316 --> 00:21:39,443
Maybe because
I didn't see it coming at all.

148
00:21:41,195 --> 00:21:43,864
It's natural that you come and you go.

149
00:21:45,157 --> 00:21:49,411
But I wish everyone could leave
at the right time.

150
00:21:51,413 --> 00:21:53,165
When is the right time?

151
00:21:55,709 --> 00:21:56,627
At 80 years old?

152
00:21:59,087 --> 00:22:01,256
You'll feel different when you become 80.

153
00:22:01,340 --> 00:22:05,052
My grandpa used to look
at old people and say

154
00:22:05,135 --> 00:22:07,596
he didn't want to live that long.

155
00:22:07,679 --> 00:22:09,473
He would only live till 80.

156
00:22:10,307 --> 00:22:11,475
But when he turned 80,

157
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:15,646
I asked, "Grandpa, aren't you supposed
to pass away this year?"

158
00:22:15,729 --> 00:22:16,647
Then he said,

159
00:22:17,439 --> 00:22:19,233
"I don't think so."

160
00:22:22,402 --> 00:22:26,114
Just like that,
he managed to live until he was 90.

161
00:22:26,198 --> 00:22:29,201
And he still said it wasn't time yet.

162
00:22:30,035 --> 00:22:32,037
What if we have a system

163
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:36,792
where all humans live up to 100?

164
00:22:37,501 --> 00:22:40,003
And die when they turn 100?

165
00:22:40,087 --> 00:22:43,215
Then I'll form a militia when I'm 99.

166
00:22:43,298 --> 00:22:45,092
"Destroy the system!"

167
00:22:45,175 --> 00:22:48,679
I'll run from the system
into the mountains.

168
00:22:57,813 --> 00:23:00,857
There's no such thing as the right time.

169
00:23:02,442 --> 00:23:04,653
But your mother chose a good day.

170
00:23:05,237 --> 00:23:06,446
Friday, Saturday, Sunday.

171
00:23:07,739 --> 00:23:09,825
We got three days off thanks to your mom.

172
00:23:10,575 --> 00:23:12,703
Gi-jeong and her boyfriend, too.

173
00:23:14,705 --> 00:23:16,373
No matter how you look at it,

174
00:23:17,874 --> 00:23:20,127
Gi-jeong's the luckiest one here, right?

175
00:23:20,210 --> 00:23:21,503
Listen.

176
00:23:22,337 --> 00:23:25,299
It would have been shameless
if she was looking for a guy to date

177
00:23:25,382 --> 00:23:27,175
after her mother passed away.

178
00:23:27,259 --> 00:23:31,680
But it's as if she knew
something like this was going to happen.

179
00:23:31,763 --> 00:23:33,307
It was as if she was possessed.

180
00:23:33,390 --> 00:23:34,808
Can you believe her?

181
00:23:34,891 --> 00:23:39,271
Pretending to have lost
her memories after getting rejected.

182
00:23:40,022 --> 00:23:43,775
She was so desperate.
She grabbed onto him in such a hurry.

183
00:23:45,736 --> 00:23:48,405
And then her mom passed away.

184
00:23:51,491 --> 00:23:53,577
So now,

185
00:23:53,660 --> 00:23:58,999
she would be blameless
if she decided to move out.

186
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:01,626
I can feel it.

187
00:24:03,128 --> 00:24:04,963
Gi-jeong will move out soon.

188
00:24:06,131 --> 00:24:09,634
Seeing that her boyfriend has visited
for three days in a row,

189
00:24:11,428 --> 00:24:12,387
I can tell.

190
00:24:12,471 --> 00:24:13,430
Yes.

191
00:24:13,513 --> 00:24:14,890
Right.

192
00:24:14,973 --> 00:24:16,850
And Chang-hee also quit his job

193
00:24:16,933 --> 00:24:20,020
-at the perfect time, right?
-Yes.

194
00:24:30,614 --> 00:24:31,907
Seriously…

195
00:24:32,741 --> 00:24:35,869
Isn't my sixth sense amazing?

196
00:24:39,039 --> 00:24:42,334
That must have been
why I wanted to quit so badly.

197
00:24:43,001 --> 00:24:47,631
But in retrospect,
I didn't want to quit that badly.

198
00:24:48,632 --> 00:24:51,468
It just felt like the right time to quit.

199
00:24:54,054 --> 00:24:56,473
I guess my soul just knew.

200
00:25:00,102 --> 00:25:01,686
If I weren't unemployed,

201
00:25:03,146 --> 00:25:04,773
who would take care of my dad?

202
00:25:08,652 --> 00:25:12,656
After the three of us go to work,
and without Gu, he'd be all by himself.

203
00:25:18,078 --> 00:25:20,080
The thought makes me tear up.

204
00:25:26,628 --> 00:25:28,547
I was like this when I was younger, too.

205
00:25:29,589 --> 00:25:31,967
When I was in high school,
my homeroom teacher said

206
00:25:32,050 --> 00:25:34,928
we'd be in trouble if anyone skipped
the after-school classes.

207
00:25:35,011 --> 00:25:37,806
I had never skipped them before,

208
00:25:37,889 --> 00:25:40,684
but I really wanted to
go home that day for some reason.

209
00:25:41,309 --> 00:25:44,896
It wasn't like I had anything to do
at home. I just wanted to go home.

210
00:25:44,980 --> 00:25:46,273
So I did.

211
00:25:47,023 --> 00:25:48,483
My grandma was alone at home.

212
00:25:49,985 --> 00:25:51,570
When I said, "I'm home,"

213
00:25:51,653 --> 00:25:54,281
her eyes were open,
but she wouldn't answer me.

214
00:25:54,823 --> 00:25:56,533
Something felt off.

215
00:25:57,534 --> 00:26:00,871
I felt like I had to
hold her hand so I did.

216
00:26:01,580 --> 00:26:02,747
But soon,

217
00:26:04,166 --> 00:26:05,792
I got the chills,

218
00:26:07,627 --> 00:26:09,254
and thought, "She must be gone."

219
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:14,134
I suddenly got scared,
so I pulled my hand away.

220
00:26:15,093 --> 00:26:16,803
Then I thought, "This isn't right."

221
00:26:17,596 --> 00:26:20,515
So I held her hand tight again.

222
00:26:20,599 --> 00:26:23,602
About five minutes later,

223
00:26:23,685 --> 00:26:25,645
my dad came back.

224
00:26:25,729 --> 00:26:27,898
"Where did you go, leaving Grandma alone?"

225
00:26:28,523 --> 00:26:32,319
It was the first time in my life
telling Dad off like that.

226
00:26:33,403 --> 00:26:36,823
He couldn't say a thing
and just listened to me.

227
00:26:38,408 --> 00:26:39,868
And it kind of felt

228
00:26:40,827 --> 00:26:41,953
cathartic.

229
00:26:46,124 --> 00:26:48,084
If I hadn't skipped school that day,

230
00:26:48,877 --> 00:26:50,962
my grandma would've passed away all alone.

231
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:55,884
Just like this, my soul knows
and my body just follows.

232
00:27:10,732 --> 00:27:11,691
I never thought…

233
00:27:14,903 --> 00:27:18,114
I would be waiting
for Gi-jeong to come home.

234
00:27:21,826 --> 00:27:24,955
After spending the whole day
with my dad alone,

235
00:27:26,540 --> 00:27:28,416
when Gi-jeong and Mi-jeong come home…

236
00:27:31,127 --> 00:27:32,212
it feels

237
00:27:34,005 --> 00:27:35,090
less lonely.

238
00:27:53,233 --> 00:27:54,651
When you feel lonely,

239
00:27:54,734 --> 00:28:00,156
I hope you remember that Oh Du-hwan
is also feeling lonely somewhere.

240
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:02,868
And this song is for us.

241
00:28:07,038 --> 00:28:09,916
<i>I didn't say</i>

242
00:28:11,001 --> 00:28:15,380
<i>Or do anything</i>

243
00:28:16,089 --> 00:28:22,304
<i>Just your name alone
Makes my heart ache</i>

244
00:28:23,221 --> 00:28:29,144
<i>Why didn't I know
That you'd be leaving so far away</i>

245
00:28:29,227 --> 00:28:34,900
<i>My love
I guess this is our goodbye</i>

246
00:28:36,151 --> 00:28:42,949
<i>The times I've sulked at you
Without good reason</i>

247
00:28:44,075 --> 00:28:50,040
<i>And the times I've been
Too harsh and negligent</i>

248
00:28:50,665 --> 00:28:56,755
<i>I never got to tell you
How sorry I am</i>

249
00:28:56,838 --> 00:29:03,094
<i>My love
I guess this is our goodbye</i>

250
00:29:04,596 --> 00:29:11,186
<i>No matter how many times I tell myself</i>

251
