00:55:54,512 --> 00:55:56,555
Why are you ignoring me
after proposing to me?

505
00:55:57,139 --> 00:55:59,183
You're not even answering my calls.

506
00:55:59,266 --> 00:56:00,518
I've been busy.

507
00:56:08,192 --> 00:56:09,151
<i>Hey.</i>

508
00:56:10,903 --> 00:56:12,405
<i>I'm not dead yet.</i>

509
00:56:14,615 --> 00:56:17,368
I knew it, you two.

510
00:56:18,119 --> 00:56:21,247
Don't worry about it.
Hyeon-a won't say yes, anyway.

511
00:56:21,330 --> 00:56:22,832
What if she does?

512
00:56:24,708 --> 00:56:26,043
He says you won't say yes.

513
00:56:27,002 --> 00:56:28,170
I will.

514
00:56:30,714 --> 00:56:32,007
She said yes.

515
00:56:32,091 --> 00:56:34,009
I need to make dinner.

516
00:56:34,093 --> 00:56:36,721
Did you see the link I sent?

517
00:56:38,013 --> 00:56:39,306
The columbarium.

518
00:56:40,766 --> 00:56:42,852
<i>I did some research,</i>

519
00:56:43,978 --> 00:56:46,897
and that's the best place. And it's clean.

520
00:56:48,357 --> 00:56:50,192
Let's put your mom's urn there.

521
00:56:50,776 --> 00:56:52,445
<i>I want mine to be there, too.</i>

522
00:56:53,654 --> 00:56:56,240
I want to go wherever you put your mom.

523
00:56:56,323 --> 00:56:58,325
You should stay with your mom.

524
00:56:59,034 --> 00:57:01,287
My mom is going to live very long.

525
00:57:02,079 --> 00:57:03,873
And I'm not expecting any visitors.

526
00:57:06,542 --> 00:57:10,755
You'll come see me
if I'm placed next to your mom.

527
00:57:13,299 --> 00:57:16,135
I'll reserve spots
for you and Hyeon-a, too.

528
00:57:16,218 --> 00:57:19,096
So you're going to take us with you?

529
00:57:19,847 --> 00:57:21,974
No, you guys take your time.

530
00:57:23,392 --> 00:57:26,353
Let's stay together, even when we're dead.

531
00:57:26,937 --> 00:57:28,355
So that we won't be bored.

532
00:57:33,944 --> 00:57:35,112
What about Mi-jeong?

533
00:57:35,946 --> 00:57:37,031
What about her?

534
00:57:37,823 --> 00:57:40,159
Is she doing all right?

535
00:57:41,327 --> 00:57:44,538
You should ask her yourself.
Aren't you closer to her than me?

536
00:57:51,796 --> 00:57:52,880
Chang-hee.

537
00:57:54,298 --> 00:57:55,508
<i>I…</i>

538
00:57:58,552 --> 00:58:00,596
need people who are happy.

539
00:58:04,683 --> 00:58:05,935
<i>So, Chang-hee…</i>

540
00:58:08,771 --> 00:58:10,731
you have to be happy.

541
00:58:16,070 --> 00:58:18,155
I carry on thanks to you.

542
00:58:54,525 --> 00:58:55,484
Dad.

543
00:58:57,319 --> 00:58:58,445
Don't worry.

544
00:58:58,529 --> 00:58:59,655
We'll…

545
00:59:00,614 --> 00:59:01,949
be even happier.

546
00:59:08,038 --> 00:59:08,956
But…

547
00:59:10,416 --> 00:59:12,418
for a family of four to be happy…

548
00:59:14,587 --> 00:59:16,005
we need a car.

549
00:59:36,191 --> 00:59:39,153
I think it's my first time
coming to the beach with Dad.

550
00:59:39,236 --> 00:59:41,947
It's the first time we've come
to the beach as a family.

551
00:59:42,031 --> 00:59:43,866
When it was just you and me,

552
00:59:43,949 --> 00:59:46,243
I have memories of going places
with Mom and Dad.

553
00:59:46,327 --> 00:59:48,954
But nothing after Mi-jeong was born.

554
00:59:50,706 --> 00:59:55,377
It's because it was hard for all five
of us to go around on buses and trains.

555
00:59:56,253 --> 00:59:58,547
That's not the reason.

556
00:59:58,631 --> 01:00:02,676
It's because Auntie got into trouble then.
And ever since then, nothing.

557
01:00:04,136 --> 01:00:07,306
The villain of our family is Auntie.

558
01:00:08,807 --> 01:00:11,185
That sounds scary.
I'm going to be an aunt one day.

559
01:00:12,061 --> 01:00:16,565
Hey, it's not possible for us
to become an aunt who robs her family.

560
01:00:16,649 --> 01:00:18,442
Dad loved her, you know?

561
01:00:18,525 --> 01:00:21,153
That's why he cared for her
and sold off his own land.

562
01:00:21,654 --> 01:00:23,822
But this asshole doesn't love us
that much.

563
01:00:23,906 --> 01:00:25,324
You have no idea.

564
01:00:25,908 --> 01:00:28,035
I would give you everything
if I had anything.

565
01:00:28,118 --> 01:00:29,453
I just can't because I don't.

566
01:00:29,536 --> 01:00:33,082
Hey. Once we get married,
let's not bother each other over money.

567
01:00:33,165 --> 01:00:35,334
Yes. Let's not ever do that.

568
01:00:36,085 --> 01:00:36,961
Never mind.

569
01:00:37,503 --> 01:00:38,796
Bother me.

570
01:00:40,047 --> 01:00:42,341
On second thought,
I think I'd give you money, too.

571
01:00:43,550 --> 01:00:44,927
But you need to know this.

572
01:00:45,469 --> 01:00:47,471
We can do that because we love each other.

573
01:00:47,554 --> 01:00:50,015
But do you think our children
will love us that much?

574
01:00:50,099 --> 01:00:52,267
I don't think so, you know?
That's the problem.

575
01:00:52,893 --> 01:00:57,231
Dad loved Aunt, but we didn't.
That's the problem.

576
01:00:57,314 --> 01:01:01,694
That's why they say you can get away
with anything if you have love.

577
01:01:33,392 --> 01:01:34,810
You still have

578
01:01:35,394 --> 01:01:38,188
the three of us by your side, Dad.

579
01:01:42,735 --> 01:01:43,902
Dad…

580
01:01:47,031 --> 01:01:48,449
I love you.

581
01:02:31,366 --> 01:02:35,412
I thought I was taking
care of them all this time.

582
01:02:37,122 --> 01:02:39,625
I only realized after she passed away…

583
01:02:41,502 --> 01:02:44,129
that Hye-suk and the kids

584
01:02:44,797 --> 01:02:47,800
were the ones taking care of me.

585
01:03:07,027 --> 01:03:09,947
YEOM MI-JEONG

586
01:03:20,874 --> 01:03:21,959
You're…

587
01:03:23,127 --> 01:03:24,753
doing well, right?

588
01:03:28,507 --> 01:03:29,675
Yes, sir.

589
01:03:53,198 --> 01:03:55,701
YEOM MI-JEONG

590
01:04:20,976 --> 01:04:22,853
I'm not sad at all.

591
01:04:27,191 --> 01:04:29,026
But why do I keep tearing up?

592
01:05:39,513 --> 01:05:40,347
<i>Hello?</i>

593
01:05:44,768 --> 01:05:45,769
<i>Hello?</i>

594
01:05:46,520 --> 01:05:47,646
It's been a while.

595
01:05:51,024 --> 01:05:52,067
It's Gu.

596
01:05:57,239 --> 01:05:58,573
<i>It has been a while.</i>

597
01:06:00,742 --> 01:06:02,119
How have you been?

598
01:06:04,663 --> 01:06:06,415
Have you managed to liberate yourself?

599
01:06:08,000 --> 01:06:09,126
<i>Of course not.</i>

600
01:06:14,589 --> 01:06:16,717
Have you met someone who worships you?

601
01:06:19,803 --> 01:06:20,846
<i>Of course not.</i>

602
01:06:24,808 --> 01:06:25,809
Let's meet up.

603
01:06:27,936 --> 01:06:29,146
<i>I can't.</i>

604
01:06:30,939 --> 01:06:31,815
Why?

605
01:06:36,028 --> 01:06:37,279
<i>I've gained weight.</i>

606
01:06:38,030 --> 01:06:39,448
<i>I need to lose some weight.</i>

607
01:06:43,368 --> 01:06:45,370
Lose some weight in an hour and meet me.

608
01:07:51,144 --> 01:07:52,771
You haven't gained much.

609
01:08:05,826 --> 01:08:06,660
What?

610
01:08:10,163 --> 01:08:12,541
You've grown your hair.

611
01:08:18,171 --> 01:08:19,589
Aren't I handsome?

612
01:08:24,719 --> 01:08:26,054
And you've cut your hair.

613
01:08:27,097 --> 01:08:28,306
Yes, a little.

614
01:08:31,476 --> 01:08:32,727
You changed your number.

615
01:08:33,979 --> 01:08:35,105
That was a bold move.

616
01:08:41,570 --> 01:08:43,613
I was so angry waiting for you to call.

617
01:08:45,824 --> 01:08:48,118
It's not like you don't know where I live.

618
01:08:48,201 --> 01:08:50,620
I thought you'd be able to
if you really wanted to.

619
01:08:52,873 --> 01:08:55,459
You never called my previous number.

620
01:08:56,668 --> 01:08:57,544
Did you?

621
01:09:03,175 --> 01:09:05,385
I missed you. So much.

622
01:09:09,097 --> 01:09:10,891
It sounds real now that I've said it.

623
01:09:12,976 --> 01:09:14,936
It feels like I really missed you so much.

624
01:09:20,775 --> 01:09:24,196
I wanted to squeeze you
and swallow you down in one mouthful.

625
01:09:30,243 --> 01:09:32,037
Aren't I good at worshiping now?

626
01:09:43,048 --> 01:09:44,633
What is your name?

627
01:09:46,218 --> 01:09:49,054
It's Gu Ja-gyeong.

628
01:10:09,943 --> 01:10:13,697
Subtitle translation by: Yoon-jung Song

629
01:10:20,141 --> 01:10:23,440
MY LIBERATION NOTES

630
01:10:23,630 --> 01:10:25,507
Why didn't you call me sooner?

631
01:10:27,717 --> 01:10:31,513
<i>He'd never let me hit rock bottom.</i>

632
01:10:31,596 --> 01:10:33,139
Do you want a part-time job?

633
01:10:33,807 --> 01:10:35,892
<i>We agreed to get married
when she turns 20.</i>

634
01:10:35,976 --> 01:10:40,188
But when she's 20, I'll be 50. Damn it.

635
01:10:40,814 --> 01:10:42,524
<i>Didn't you say
it was over between you two?</i>

636
01:10:42,607 --> 01:10:44,776
I've always known
what kind of a person you are.

637
01:10:44,859 --> 01:10:46,069
<i>I'll be here for you.</i>

638
01:10:47,362 --> 01:10:49,155
<i>-What?
-You son of a bitch!</i>

639
01:10:49,239 --> 01:10:50,657
<i>When I met you again,</i>

640
01:10:50,740 --> 01:10:51,950
<i>I regretted it.</i>

641
01:10:52,033 --> 01:10:53,451
<i>I do see</i>

642
01:10:53,535 --> 01:10:54,452
a doctor.

643
01:10:55,579 --> 01:10:56,663
<i>Just go.</i>

644
01:10:57,163 --> 01:10:58,331
<i>I'll stay.</i>

645
01:10:59,874 --> 01:11:02,002
<i>Remember this one thing.</i>

